Title: Forecast Eurovision Voting
Subtitle: This competition requires contestants to forecast the voting for this year's Eurovision Song Contest in Norway on May 25th, 27th and 29th.

Title: Predict HIV Progression
Subtitle: This contest requires competitors to predict the likelihood that an HIV patient's infection will become less severe, given a small dataset and limited clinical information.

Title: World Cup 2010 - Take on the Quants
Subtitle: Quants at Goldman Sachs and JP Morgan have modeled the likely outcomes of the 2010 World Cup. Can you do better?

Title: INFORMS Data Mining Contest 2010
Subtitle: The goal of this contest is to predict short term movements in stock prices. The winners of this contest will be honoured of the INFORMS Annual Meeting in Austin-Texas (November 7-10).

Title: World Cup 2010 - Confidence Challenge
Subtitle: The Confidence Challenge requires competitors to assign a level of confidence to their World Cup predictions.

Title: Predict Grant Applications
Subtitle: This task requires participants to predict the outcome of grant applications for the University of Melbourne.

Title: Chess ratings - Elo versus the Rest of the World
Subtitle: This competition aims to discover whether other approaches can predict the outcome of chess games more accurately than the workhorse Elo rating system.

Title: Tourism Forecasting Part One
Subtitle: Part one requires competitors to predict 518 tourism-related time series. The winner of this competition will be invited to contribute a discussion paper to the International Journal of Forecasting.

Title: Tourism Forecasting Part Two
Subtitle: Part two requires competitors to predict 793 tourism-related time series. The winner of this competition will be invited to contribute a discussion paper to the International Journal of Forecasting.

Title: R Package Recommendation Engine
Subtitle: The aim of this competition is to develop a recommendation engine for R libraries (or packages). (R is opensource statistics software.)

Title: IJCNN Social Network Challenge
Subtitle: This competition requires participants to predict edges in an online social network. The winner will receive free registration and the opportunity to present their solution at IJCNN 2011.

Title: RTA Freeway Travel Time Prediction
Subtitle: This competition requires participants to predict travel time on Sydney's M4 freeway from past travel time observations.

Title: Stay Alert! The Ford Challenge
Subtitle: Driving while not alert can be deadly. The objective is to design a classifier that will detect whether the driver is alert or not alert, employing data that are acquired while driving.

Title: Deloitte/FIDE Chess Rating Challenge
Subtitle: This contest, sponsored by professional services firm Deloitte, will find the most accurate system to predict chess outcomes, and FIDE will also bring a top finisher to Athens to present their system

Title: Mapping Dark Matter
Subtitle: Measure the small distortion in galaxy images caused by dark matter

Title: ICDAR 2011 - Arabic Writer Identification
Subtitle: This competition require participants to develop an algorithm to identify who wrote which documents. The winner will be honored at a special session of the ICDAR 2011 conference.

Title: Don't Overfit!
Subtitle: With nearly as many variables as training cases, what are the best techniques to avoid disaster?

Title: Heritage Health Prize
Subtitle: Identify patients who will be admitted to a hospital within the next year using historical claims data. (Enter by 06:59:59 UTC Oct 4 2012)

Title: Wikipedia's Participation Challenge
Subtitle: This competition challenges data-mining experts to build a predictive model that predicts the number of edits an editor will make five months from the end date of the training dataset.

Title: Allstate Claim Prediction Challenge
Subtitle: A key part of insurance is charging each customer the appropriate price for the risk they represent.

Title: dunnhumby's Shopper Challenge
Subtitle: Going grocery shopping, we all have to do it, some even enjoy it, but can you predict it? dunnhumby is looking to build a model to better predict when supermarket shoppers will next visit the store and how much they will spend.

Title: Semi-Supervised Feature Learning
Subtitle: Find methods which work best on large-scale, high-dimensional learning tasks

Title: Give Me Some Credit
Subtitle: Improve on the state of the art in credit scoring by predicting the probability that somebody will experience financial distress in the next two years.

Title: UCL CoMPLEX MRes module
Subtitle: This contest requires competitors to predict the likelihood that an HIV patient's infection will become less severe, given a small dataset and limited clinical information.

Title: UCL Applied Machine Learning 2
Subtitle: Film recommendation problem

Title: UW STAT331 Linear Models Contest
Subtitle: Students are to apply their techniques discussed in class to make the best predictions possible. Feature selection is a major theme.

Title: UMICH SI650 - Sentiment Classification
Subtitle: This is an in-class contest hosted by University of Michigan SI650 (Information Retrieval)

Title: Erasmus University Rotterdam - Econometrie 2  - Prediction Competition
Subtitle: Use the techniques discussed in class to find the regression model that makes the best predictions.

Title: Don't Get Kicked!
Subtitle: Predict if a car purchased at auction is a lemon

Title: Algorithmic Trading Challenge
Subtitle: Develop new models to accurately predict the market response to large trades.

Title: CHALEARN Gesture Challenge
Subtitle: Develop a Gesture Recognizer for Microsoft Kinect (TM)

Title: What Do You Know?
Subtitle: Improve the state of the art in student evaluation by predicting whether a student will answer the next test question correctly.

Title: Photo Quality Prediction
Subtitle: Given anonymized information on thousands of photo albums, predict whether a human evaluator would mark them as 'good'.

Title: First International Competition of Time Series Forecasting
Subtitle: We seek to evaluate the accuracy of computational intelligence methods in time series forecasting with multiple frequencies.

Title: The Hewlett Foundation: Automated Essay Scoring
Subtitle: Develop an automated scoring algorithm for student-written essays.

Title: Mineria de Datos Uniandes
Subtitle: Concurso para aplicar las técnicas aprendidas en la clase de Minería de Datos.

Title: UCI Math77B: Collaborative Filtering
Subtitle: Did you laugh?  Predict whether a joke is funny for Math 77B Collaborative Filtering at UCI!

Title: Benchmark Bond Trade Price Challenge
Subtitle: Develop models to accurately predict the trade price of a bond.

Title: Eye Movements Verification and Identification Competition
Subtitle: Determine how people may be identified based on their eye movement characteristic.

Title: KDD Cup 2012, Track 1
Subtitle: Predict which users (or information sources) one user might follow in Tencent Weibo.

Title: KDD Cup 2012, Track 2
Subtitle: Predict the click-through rate of ads given the query and user information.

Title: Обнаружение веб-спама
Subtitle: Соревнование в рамках курса ШАД "Веб-Графы"

Title: GigaOM WordPress Challenge: Splunk Innovation Prospect
Subtitle: Predict which blog posts someone will like.

Title: ICFHR 2012 - Arabic Writer Identification
Subtitle: Identify which writer wrote which documents.

Title: Predicting a Biological Response
Subtitle: Predict a biological response of molecules from their chemical properties

Title: Million Song Dataset Challenge
Subtitle: Predict which songs a user will listen to.

Title: Ecopetrol
Subtitle: Tiene como objetivo implementar un modelo de clasificacion

Title: Online Product Sales
Subtitle: Predict the online sales of a consumer product based on a data set of product features.

Title: Psychopathy Prediction Based on Twitter Usage
Subtitle: Identify people who have a high degree of Psychopathy based on Twitter usage.

Title: Raising Money to Fund an Organizational Mission
Subtitle: Help worthy organizations more efficiently target and recruit loyal donors to support their causes.
